# Build context exclusions. Without this file the entire repository
# (including target/, artifacts/, .git/, dist/, node_modules/) is sent to
# the Docker daemon every build — slow on the wire and a frequent
# source of cargo-chef cache invalidation.
#
# Rule of thumb: anything under .gitignore should be here too, plus a few
# extra dev artefacts that *aren't* gitignored but never belong in an
# image.

# Build artefacts (any cargo / Rust target dir, including the historical
# workaround locations Phase 1.6 removed)
target/
.cargo-cache-docker/
target-docker/

# Front-end build outputs
**/dist/
**/pkg/
**/node_modules/

# IDE / OS junk
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store

# Local git metadata — never needed in an image and changes constantly,
# defeating layer caching of `COPY . .`.
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Bench / measurement output (writes happen during dev, would otherwise
# break cargo-chef's `cacher` layer cache because mtime changes propagate
# through `COPY . .` in `planner` / `builder`).
artifacts/

# Lefthook + local secrets
.lefthook-local.yml
.env
.env.local

# Markdown-only changes don't need to invalidate the image either —
# keep them out of the build context.
*.md
docs/
